  39,1,"The revelation of the Book [occurs] through God, the Powerful, the Wise"
  39,2,"We have sent the Book down to you with the Truth, so serve God sincerely: religion belongs to Him"
  39,3,"Pure religion belongs to God [Alone]! The ones who take on [other] patrons instead of Him [claim]: \"We do not serve them except to bring closer to God in homage.\" God will judge among them about whatever they have been differing over; God does not guide anyone who is disbelieving liar"
  39,4,"If God had wanted to adopt a son, He would select an one He wished from what He has created. Glory be to Him! He is God Alone, the Irresistible"
  39,5,"He has created Heaven and Earth for Truth. He wraps night up in daytime, and wraps daytime up in night. He regulates the sun and moon: each runs along on a specific course. Is He not the Powerful, the Forgiving"